{{other uses|Malignancy (disambiguation)}}
'''Malignants''' is a name used for the advisors of [[Charles I of England]], chief among whom were
[[Thomas Wentworth, 1st Earl of Strafford|Thomas Wentworth, 1st Earl Strafford]] and [[William Laud]], Archbishop of Canterbury. The term was used by the [[Parliament of England|Parliamentarians]], who blamed them for the evils of the country; the name was afterwards applied to the whole [[Cavalier|Royalist]] party.{{sfn|Wood|1907|loc="Malignants"}}

